			</classificationInformation>
			<CASNumber>CID 23266</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sodium silicate, often called 'water glass', is the most important of the soluble silicates. It is ordinarily supplied as a colorless, viscous water solution displaying little tack. It is used as a spin-on adhesive layer to bond glass to glass or silicon oxide covered silicon wafers to one another. This material can withstand temperatures of up to 1100 °C. Although non-toxic, it may pose harm to the skin and eyes, and inhalation can lead to respiratory problems.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硅酸钠通常被称为 &quot;水玻璃&quot;，是最重要的可溶性硅酸盐。它通常以无色粘稠水溶液的形式供应，粘性很小。它可用作旋涂粘合剂层，将玻璃与玻璃或覆盖氧化硅的硅晶片相互粘合在一起。这种材料可承受高达 1100 °C 的温度。虽然无毒，但可能会对皮肤和眼睛造成伤害，吸入后可能会导致呼吸问题。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Na2SiO3 or Na2O3Si</sumFormula>
